cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.SE, cs.Distributed, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses a framework for dynamic resizing and scheduling of parallel applications on distributed memory platforms, which falls under the scope of distributed and parallel computing. 
2. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper focuses on improving the overall system throughput and individual job turn-around time, which is related to performance optimization. 
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper presents a software framework for dynamic resizing and scheduling of parallel applications, which falls under the scope of software engineering. 
4. cs.Distributed - The paper discusses a framework for dynamic resizing and scheduling of parallel applications on distributed memory platforms, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the use of an API to enable applications to interact with the scheduler, which falls under the scope of programming languages.
